text.tspan: Global meat demand if everyone ate like the average citizen of..., 1961 to
Hypothetical global meat demand if everyone in the world ate the same quantity as the average citizen of a given country, e.g.
data for the USA in 1990 hypothesises global meat demand if everyone in the world consumed the same amount of meat as
the average US citizen in 1990. Actual global meat production in 2013 was 310 million tonnes.
Source: OWID based on FAO & UN
